definition.value: A branched trisaccharide that is alpha-L-Fucp-(1->3)-alpha-D-Galp in which the hydroxy group at position 4 of the D-galactopyranose moiety has been glycosylated by an alpha-D-glucopyranosyl group.
A disaccharide that is D-mannopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 4 has been converted into the corresponding beta-D-galactopyranosyl derivative.
A glycosylmannose that is D-mannopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 3 has been converted into the corresponding beta-D-galactofuranosyl derivative.
A glycosylgalactose consisting of alpha-D-galactofuranose and D-galactopyranose joined in sequence by a (1->2) glycosidic bond.
A glycosylxylose consisting of beta-D-glucopyranuronic acid and D-xylopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->4) glycosidic bond.
